722342f.title: Manhattan: Park Avenue - 77th Street
722342f.text:
850 Park Avenue, S. W. corner 77th Street. This and the next
buildin to the south were erected between 1910 end 1916.
About 1919.
Collins, Photogrepher.

714530f-a.title: Manhattan: 77th Street (East) - Park Avenue
714530f-a.text:
E. 77th Street, north side, east from Park to Lexington
Avenues, and showing in the foreground a square granite buildin8s
(No. 103-05, the 8th Ch rch of Christ Scientist) and a frame
structure (No. 1O7) to the east. The 3 story structures beyond
the latter are garages with quarters above. The 12 story anart-
ment house (No. ll7-119) seen, replaced 2 five story tenements
that stood in 1922.
July 21, 1937.
P.L. Sperr

714531f-a.title: Manhattan: 77th Street (East) - Park Avenue
714531f-a.text:
107 East 77th Street, north side, east of Park Avenue. This
is a two-story frame house.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 242.
